Ollama and Llama sound similar, but they are completely different things.

Think of it like this:

Llama = The AI brain (Model)
Ollama = The software that runs the AI brain on your computer
Simple Analogy

Imagine you want to watch a movie.

🎬 Movie = Llama Model
📺 VLC Media Player = Ollama

Without VLC, the movie cannot play.

Without the movie, VLC has nothing to play.

Exactly the same.

===

What is Llama?

Llama (Large Language Model Meta AI) is an AI model developed by Meta.

It understands language and can:

Answer questions
Write emails
Generate code
Translate languages
Summarize documents
Analyze text

It is similar to:

ChatGPT (OpenAI)
Gemini (Google)
Claude (Anthropic)
Mistral
DeepSeek

Llama is only the trained AI model.

It is not software.

Example

You ask:

Write an email for leave.

Llama thinks like this:

Input
 ↓
Understand English
 ↓
Generate response
 ↓
Output Email

Llama itself doesn't know how to open files or create windows.

It only predicts the next word.

====
What is Ollama?

Ollama is software that lets you download and run AI models locally on your own computer.

Instead of using ChatGPT online,

you can run

Llama
Mistral
Gemma
DeepSeek
Phi
Qwen

offline using Ollama.

====

Ollama is like
Spotify

plays songs.

Similarly,

Ollama

plays AI models.

